I have a use case for something like this SASS mixin. Would be useful to be able to iterate a styles object and have reference to the key and value.

```@mixin myMixin($str){
  $prop : (
    color:red,
    border:1px solid red,
    position:relative
  );
  @each $key, $value in $prop {
    #{$key}: #{$value} #{$str};
  }
}
p{
    @include myMixin(!important);
}```
The difference with my particular use case is that `$prop` would be a styles object passed as an argument to the Macro
